rComments: I had Dr. Maly for Introductory Philosophy in 1986 and because of him I majored in the discipline and eventually earned a PhD.  He is a fantastic teacher and friend.  He makes it possible for everyone who tries to get at least a C.  He opened up a world of introspection that I have benefitted from my whole life.  Thank you, Dr. Maly.
One of the best professors I have ever had. Funny, insightful, concerned, engaged.

One of the best professors I have ever had.  Very thought provoking, always challenging students and provoking challenges.  He loves discussions in class and tells some great jokes too!  I had an awesome time with existentialism in his class.

The best prof I've had in four years.  Funny, engaging, thought provoking.  Truly wants to change how we think, and the world by doing so.  Highly recommended for anyone who wants a prof with passion.  But as he says "Don't trust my word for it.  Check it out!"

BEST prof I ever had, and most likely will remain the BEST in my list.  He cares so much about his students and always make himself available.  For my final paper, I couldn't finish on time, he gave me extension with no penality. Course material itself is somewhat difficult, but GreAT teacher. Take his courses, you'll love him!

He is funny and enthusiastic. The readings are interesting but repetetive. Unfortunately the lectures only confuse and boggle anything that was learned from the readings. Marking is inconsistent, and dependant on TA's. A huge number of those who got an A on the first test dropped to a C or even a D for the second.
